.SS "const uint32_t SEQUENCE_FINAL = 0xffffffff\fR [static]\fP"
Setting nSequence to this value for every input in a transaction disables nLockTime/IsFinalTx()\&. It fails OP_CHECKLOCKTIMEVERIFY/CheckLockTime() for any input that has it set (BIP 65)\&. It has SEQUENCE_LOCKTIME_DISABLE_FLAG set (BIP 68/112)\&. 
.SS "const uint32_t SEQUENCE_LOCKTIME_DISABLE_FLAG = (1U << 31)\fR [static]\fP"
If this flag is set, \fBCTxIn::nSequence\fP is NOT interpreted as a relative lock-time\&. It skips \fBSequenceLocks()\fP for any input that has it set (BIP 68)\&. It fails OP_CHECKSEQUENCEVERIFY/CheckSequence() for any input that has it set (BIP 112)\&. 
.SS "const int SEQUENCE_LOCKTIME_GRANULARITY = 9\fR [static]\fP"
In order to use the same number of bits to encode roughly the same wall-clock duration, and because blocks are naturally limited to occur every 600s on average, the minimum granularity for time-based relative lock-time is fixed at 512 seconds\&. Converting from \fBCTxIn::nSequence\fP to seconds is performed by multiplying by 512 = 2^9, or equivalently shifting up by 9 bits\&. 
.SS "const uint32_t SEQUENCE_LOCKTIME_MASK = 0x0000ffff\fR [static]\fP"
If \fBCTxIn::nSequence\fP encodes a relative lock-time, this mask is applied to extract that lock-time from the sequence field\&. 
.SS "const uint32_t SEQUENCE_LOCKTIME_TYPE_FLAG = (1 << 22)\fR [static]\fP"
If \fBCTxIn::nSequence\fP encodes a relative lock-time and this flag is set, the relative lock-time has units of 512 seconds, otherwise it specifies blocks with a granularity of 1\&. 

